  "prompt": "What songs (of any genre) have the word \"Boogie\" in the title and/or in the lyrics?",
  "response": "The word \"Boogie\" has been used in numerous songs across various genres, often reflecting a danceable, rhythmic vibe. Here\u2019s a list of notable songs that include \"Boogie\" in the title or prominently in the lyrics:\n\n### Songs with \"Boogie\" in the Title:\n1. **\"Boogie Woogie Bugle Boy\"** - The Andrews Sisters (1941)  \n   A classic WWII-era swing song about a talented bugle player.\n\n2. **\"Boogie Wonderland\"** - Earth, Wind & Fire with The Emotions (1979)  \n   A disco anthem that became a signature hit for the group.\n\n3. **\"Boogie Shoes\"** - KC and the Sunshine Band (1975)  \n   Featured in the *Saturday Night Fever* soundtrack, this song is a disco classic.\n\n4. **\"Boogie Nights\"** - Heatwave (1977)  \n   A funky disco track that became a massive hit.\n\n5. **\"Boogie Oogie Oogie\"** - A Taste of Honey (1978)  \n   A funk and disco hit that won a Grammy for Best New Artist.\n\n6. **\"Boogie in Your Butt\"** - Eddie Murphy (1982)  \n   A comedic funk track from Eddie Murphy\u2019s *Comedian* album.\n\n7. **\"Boogie Down\"** - Alton McClain and Destiny (1979)  \n   A disco and soul track with a catchy groove.\n\n8. **\"Boogie Chillen'\"** - John Lee Hooker (1948)  \n   A blues classic that laid the foundation for rock and roll.\n\n9. **\"Boogie On Reggae Woman\"** - Stevie Wonder (1974)  \n   A funk and soul track blending reggae influences.\n\n10. **\"Boogie Man\"** - AC/DC (1995)  \n    A hard rock track from the band\u2019s *Ballbreaker* album.\n\n---\n\n### Songs with \"Boogie\" in the Lyrics:\n1. **\"Proud Mary\"** - Creedence Clearwater Revival (1969)  \n   The lyrics include the line: \"Rollin\u2019, rollin\u2019, rollin\u2019 on the river... Big wheel keep on turnin\u2019, Proud Mary keep on burnin\u2019, Rollin\u2019, rollin\u2019, rollin\u2019 on the river... Doin\u2019 the boogie.\"\n\n2. **\"Bad to the Bone\"** - George Thorogood & The Destroyers (1982)  \n   The lyrics contain the line: \"I make a rich man\u2019s daughter sing the boogie woogie blues.\"\n\n3. **\"Johnny B. Goode\"** - Chuck Berry (1958)  \n   The lyrics include: \"He could play the guitar just like a-ringing a bell... Go, go, go Johnny, go, go... Go Johnny, go, go, go Johnny, go, go... Johnny B. Goode... And he did the boogie woogie all night long.\"\n\n4. **\"I\u2019m Your Boogie Man\"** - KC and the Sunshine Band (1976)  \n   The entire song is about being the \"Boogie Man\" who makes you dance.\n\n5. **\"Boogie Fever\"** - The Sylvers (1975)  \n   The lyrics revolve around the infectious \"boogie fever\" that makes everyone dance.\n\n6. **\"Boogie Shoes\"** - KC and the Sunshine Band (1975)  \n   The song is all about dancing in your \"boogie shoes.\"\n\n7. **\"Boogie Wonderland\"** - Earth, Wind & Fire with The Emotions (1979)  \n   The lyrics celebrate the joy of dancing in a \"boogie wonderland.\"\n\n---\n\n### Covers and References:\n- Many artists have covered or referenced \"Boogie Woogie Bugle Boy\" and other boogie-themed songs, keeping the term alive in pop culture.\n\nLet me know if you\u2019d like more details about any of these songs!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
